      <abstract>
        <p>Testimony of Alexander (Shlomo) Schmiedt, which was part of the Documentation campaign,
          Prague. Schmiedt was deported from Prague to the Theresienstadt ghetto in July 1942, from
          where he was sent to Auschwitz in autumn of 1944. He was liberated in the Kaufering camp.
          Schmiedt became after the war one of the main co-worker of the Documentation campaign,
          Prague. Later he emigrated to Israel.</p>
      </abstract>

